%N A386947 A variant of Recamán's sequence (A005132): a(0) = 0; for n > 0, a(n) = a(n-1) - n if nonnegative and not already in the sequence, otherwise a(n) = a(n-1) + n + 2.
%C A386947 When visualized in connecting semicircular lines (like the original Recamán Sequence, cf. Edmund Harriss, "The first 65 steps drawn as a spiral" in A005132), it appears to produce conical spirals.
%C A386947 The first repeating term is 61.
%H A386947 Jules Beauchamp, <a href="/A386947/a386947_1.png">The first 60 steps drawn as a spiral</a>.
%t A386947 a[n_] := a[n] = If[a[n-1] >= n && FreeQ[Table[a[k], {k, 0, n-1}], a[n-1] - n], a[n-1] - n, a[n-1] + n + 2]; a[0] = 0; Array[a, 100, 0] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Aug 22 2025 *)
